text:
(1) Kings Highway, north from Ave. H. At the left is the Manhattan Beach Division of the Long Island R.R. The barns etc. at right were John Ditmars. they were in existence in 1900. The dirt road now Kingshighway, was known as the Road from Flatlands to New Lots. 1922. Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2) The same, showing only the railroad. May 1922. Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(3) The same as No. 1. May 1922. Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(4) The same, looking northeast from Utica Ave. 1922. Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

*ASSUMING STREET TO BE NORTH AND SOUTH*
